6. Performance Concepts Learned
O(n squared) — Quadratic Complexity
A loop inside a loop means time grows as the square of input size. Double your data = four times slower. With 5,000 products: 25 million operations. With 10,000 products: 100 million operations. Always ask: can I avoid nested loops?

Two-Pointer Technique
When data is sorted, use two pointers moving toward each other instead of comparing every pair. One pointer starts at the cheapest product, one at the most expensive. They move inward until they meet. Turns O(n squared) into O(n).

Early Exit
Stop searching the moment you find what you need. Do not check all 25 million pairs if you only need the first 10 results. This is sometimes called short-circuit evaluation.

