Performance Analysis: Slow Code — O(n squared) Nested Loops
Problem Description
find_product_combinations() takes approximately 25 seconds for 5,000 products because of 25 million nested loop comparisons. This makes the product recommendation page too slow to load for users.

Root Cause — Three Compounding Issues
1.	Nested loops produce 25 million comparisons for 5,000 products — O(n squared) complexity
2.	Duplicate check searches ALL previous results on every valid pair found — gets slower as results grows
3.	Self-comparisons are generated then skipped instead of never being generated

Optimizations Applied
4.	Start j at i+1 — halves comparisons and eliminates duplicates in one change
5.	Remove duplicate check — no longer needed after Fix 1
6.	Two-pointer technique — reduces comparisons from 25 million to roughly 5,000

