Key Learning Points
•	Nested loops are the most common cause of slow Python code — always check for loop-inside-loop patterns
•	When you see O(n squared), ask: can I sort the data and use two pointers instead?
•	My initial observations were partially correct — I calculated 25 million comparisons correctly and knew speed would decrease, but did not know WHY or HOW to fix it
•	The duplicate check was a hidden second performance problem I would not have spotted without the AI prompt
•	Performance tools like cProfile show you exactly which line is slowest — always measure before and after optimizing
•	O(n squared) problems almost always have an O(n) solution when you sort the data first

